    <AffiliateDisclaimer />

    <p>For decades, creatine was marketed exclusively to male bodybuilders. That is changing rapidly. Research published between 2020 and 2026 has uncovered women-specific benefits that extend far beyond the gym — cognitive enhancement, bone density support, mood improvement, and post-menopausal muscle retention. Meanwhile, creatine gummies have lowered the adoption barrier with pre-dosed, portable, pleasant-tasting formats that fit seamlessly into daily routines. The result: women are the fastest-growing creatine consumer demographic, and gummies are the format driving that adoption.</p>

