      The three biggest myths keeping women from creatine — "it will make me bulky," "it causes bloating," and "it is only for men" — are all contradicted by the clinical evidence. Creatine is one of the safest, most effective, and most gender-inclusive supplements available, with over 500 studies confirming its benefits and safety profile for both sexes.
      <cite>— Sarah Mitchell, RD, CNS</cite>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Myth: Creatine causes visible bloating in women.</strong> Creatine causes <em>intracellular</em> water retention inside muscle cells — not subcutaneous (under-the-skin) bloating. The 1-3 pounds of water weight is inside your muscles, potentially making them appear fuller and more defined. It does not cause a puffy or bloated external appearance. GI-related bloating from creatine is typically caused by taking too large a dose (skip the loading phase) or consuming powder on an empty stomach — gummies avoid both issues.</p>
    </div>

